to generate the exif info
navigate to root (where index.html is)
run

exiftool -j -Model -LensModel -ISO -FNumber -ExposureTime -FocalLength -ext avif ./images > gallery-data.json

Breakdown of the Flags
-j: Formats the output as a clean JSON array (required by response.json() in your script).

-Model -LensModel ...: Explicitly requests only these specific tags. This keeps your gallery-data.json file small and efficient.

-ext avif: Tells ExifTool to only look for your new .avif files, ignoring other system files (like .DS_Store or hidden files).

./images: The source folder containing your photos.

> gallery-data.json: Saves the output into the file named gallery-data.json in your current directory (the Kimball folder).




